"{\"uid\": \"greekreporter.com-2024-07-26-paris-olympics-opening-biggest-show-earth\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympics opening ceremony on Friday night is billed as the biggest open-air show on Earth.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 100, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Paris Olympics opening ceremony\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 35}, {\"ngram\": \"Friday night\", \"from\": 39, \"to\": 51}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest open-air show\", \"from\": 65, \"to\": 90}, {\"ngram\": \"Earth\", \"from\": 94, \"to\": 99}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will be the first time the curtain-raiser for the world's biggest sporting event has taken place outside a stadium.\", \"from\": 101, \"to\": 219, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 112, \"to\": 126}, {\"ngram\": \"the curtain-raiser\", \"from\": 127, \"to\": 145}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's biggest sporting event\", \"from\": 150, \"to\": 184}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 195, \"to\": 200}, {\"ngram\": \"a stadium\", \"from\": 209, \"to\": 218}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead of the traditional parade around a stadium track, more than 8,000 of the world's top athletes will be transported by boat along 6km of the River Seine from the Austerlitz bridge to the Trocadero in a kind of sporting Armada, as more than 300,000 people watch from the bridges and riverbanks and police, frogmen and snipers stand guard.\", \"from\": 221, \"to\": 564, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 368, \"end\": 379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 389, \"end\": 399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"score\": 0.995347332057659, \"rank\": 0.004674416449654515, \"text\": \"Austerlitz\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the traditional parade\", \"from\": 232, \"to\": 254}, {\"ngram\": \"a stadium track\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 277}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's top athletes\", \"from\": 298, \"to\": 322}, {\"ngram\": \"boat\", \"from\": 346, \"to\": 350}, {\"ngram\": \"6km\", \"from\": 357, \"to\": 360}, {\"ngram\": \"the Trocadero\", \"from\": 410, \"to\": 423}, {\"ngram\": \"a kind\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 433}, {\"ngram\": \"sporting Armada\", \"from\": 437, \"to\": 452}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 300,000 people\", \"from\": 457, \"to\": 481}, {\"ngram\": \"the bridges\", \"from\": 493, \"to\": 504}, {\"ngram\": \"riverbanks\", \"from\": 509, \"to\": 519}, {\"ngram\": \"police\", \"from\": 524, \"to\": 530}, {\"ngram\": \"frogmen\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 539}, {\"ngram\": \"snipers\", \"from\": 544, \"to\": 551}, {\"ngram\": \"guard\", \"from\": 558, \"to\": 563}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first boats to sail through the River Seine will carry the Greek athletes.\", \"from\": 566, \"to\": 644, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 602, \"end\": 613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 629, \"end\": 634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.9638270185883954, \"rank\": 0.03680652647059543, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The first boats\", \"from\": 566, \"to\": 581}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Giannis Antetokounmpo who was officially appointed the flag bearer forGreeceat the Paris Olympics, alongside athlete Antigoni Drisbioti,will lead the flotilla.\", \"from\": 645, \"to\": 804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 645, \"end\": 666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giannis_Antetokounmpo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Giannis Antetokounmpo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giannis_Antetokounmpo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giannis_Antetokounmpo\"}, {\"begin\": 762, \"end\": 780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antigoni_Drisbioti\", \"score\": 0.9999999936558197, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Antigoni Drisbioti\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antigoni_Drisbioti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antigoni_Drisbioti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the flag bearer forGreeceat\", \"from\": 696, \"to\": 723}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 742}, {\"ngram\": \"athlete\", \"from\": 754, \"to\": 761}, {\"ngram\": \"the flotilla\", \"from\": 791, \"to\": 803}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The journey will take in landmarks such as the \\u00cele Saint Louis, Notre-Dame de Paris and the Louvre Museum, which will provide the backdrop for 12 artistic tableaux devised by Thomas Jolly,artistic director of the ceremony, that will unfurl like a film.\", \"from\": 806, \"to\": 1058, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 898, \"end\": 911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Louvre Museum\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}, {\"begin\": 981, \"end\": 987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9967178544825147, \"rank\": 0.0032299309177897147, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The journey\", \"from\": 806, \"to\": 817}, {\"ngram\": \"landmarks\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 840}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\u00cele Saint Louis\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 868}, {\"ngram\": \"Notre-Dame de Paris\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 889}, {\"ngram\": \"the backdrop\", \"from\": 932, \"to\": 944}, {\"ngram\": \"12 artistic tableaux\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 969}, {\"ngram\": \"artistic director\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1011}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 1015, \"to\": 1027}, {\"ngram\": \"a film\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1057}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly said the storyline will encompass the many facets of France, from the historic events that unfolded in locations such as the Conciergerie, the prison where Marie Antoinette was jailed, to the modern day, with an emphasis on diversity.\", \"from\": 1060, \"to\": 1300, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1119, \"end\": 1125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999566557221835, \"rank\": 0.00043322743692809256, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1191, \"end\": 1203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3718886342769448e-36, \"text\": \"Conciergerie\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\"}, {\"begin\": 1222, \"end\": 1238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3037311676454731e-30, \"text\": \"Marie Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the storyline\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1084}, {\"ngram\": \"the many facets\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1115}, {\"ngram\": \"the historic events\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1151}, {\"ngram\": \"locations\", \"from\": 1169, \"to\": 1178}, {\"ngram\": \"the prison\", \"from\": 1205, \"to\": 1215}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern day\", \"from\": 1254, \"to\": 1268}, {\"ngram\": \"an emphasis\", \"from\": 1275, \"to\": 1286}, {\"ngram\": \"diversity\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1299}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"History shows we have sent a lot of ideas and innovations into the world, and the world in turn has come to Paris.\", \"from\": 1302, \"to\": 1417, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1411, \"end\": 1416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.816631145949588e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"History\", \"from\": 1303, \"to\": 1310}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1335}, {\"ngram\": \"ideas\", \"from\": 1339, \"to\": 1344}, {\"ngram\": \"innovations\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1360}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1366, \"to\": 1375}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1381, \"to\": 1390}, {\"ngram\": \"turn\", \"from\": 1394, \"to\": 1398}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Seine tells the story of this great celebration of humanity, and the ceremony will reflect that,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1528, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1422, \"end\": 1427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.326179727680636e-23, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the story\", \"from\": 1434, \"to\": 1443}, {\"ngram\": \"this great celebration\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1469}, {\"ngram\": \"humanity\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1481}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1499}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the athletes glide down the river, dancers, pop stars, tightrope walkers and acrobats will perform daring feats on water, rooftops, bridges and artificial islands using pontoons, floating pianos, helicopters and possibly even submarines, before a vast laser show finale is beamed from the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1838, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1536, \"to\": 1548}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1569}, {\"ngram\": \"dancers\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1578}, {\"ngram\": \"pop stars\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1589}, {\"ngram\": \"tightrope walkers\", \"from\": 1591, \"to\": 1608}, {\"ngram\": \"acrobats\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1621}, {\"ngram\": \"daring feats\", \"from\": 1635, \"to\": 1647}, {\"ngram\": \"water\", \"from\": 1651, \"to\": 1656}, {\"ngram\": \"rooftops\", \"from\": 1658, \"to\": 1666}, {\"ngram\": \"bridges\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1675}, {\"ngram\": \"artificial islands\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1698}, {\"ngram\": \"pontoons\", \"from\": 1705, \"to\": 1713}, {\"ngram\": \"a vast laser show finale\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1805}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1837}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the athletes sail, a show will unfurl around them, described by its organizers as revolutionary and irreverent, as well as full of surprises.\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 1984, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1855}, {\"ngram\": \"a show\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 1868}, {\"ngram\": \"its organizers\", \"from\": 1907, \"to\": 1921}, {\"ngram\": \"surprises\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 1983}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the surprises installed is reportedly the performance ofLady Gaga and Celine Dion, two of the music industry's most iconic voices.\", \"from\": 1986, \"to\": 2123, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2054, \"end\": 2058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6357620760037718e-23, \"text\": \"Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}, {\"begin\": 2063, \"end\": 2074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.814342678755972e-37, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the surprises\", \"from\": 1993, \"to\": 2006}, {\"ngram\": \"the performance\", \"from\": 2031, \"to\": 2046}, {\"ngram\": \"the music industry's most iconic voices\", \"from\": 2083, \"to\": 2122}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The duo will reportedly perform the classic \\u00c9dith Piaf song \\\"La Vie en Rose.\\\"\", \"from\": 2125, \"to\": 2202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2169, \"end\": 2179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\", \"score\": 0.9999999997958184, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"\\u00c9dith Piaf\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The duo\", \"from\": 2125, \"to\": 2132}, {\"ngram\": \"La Vie\", \"from\": 2186, \"to\": 2192}, {\"ngram\": \"Rose\", \"from\": 2196, \"to\": 2200}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The choice of song, a beloved French anthem, underscores the cultural and emotional weight of the occasion.\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2310, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2233, \"end\": 2239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9046605094979533, \"rank\": 0.10213725624913148, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The choice\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2213}, {\"ngram\": \"song\", \"from\": 2217, \"to\": 2221}, {\"ngram\": \"the cultural and emotional weight\", \"from\": 2260, \"to\": 2293}, {\"ngram\": \"the occasion\", \"from\": 2297, \"to\": 2309}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The idea of performing a show of this magnitude along a large stretch of river in a city under its highest terrorism alert was so outrageous that even Emmanuel Macron at first thought it was \\\"a crazy and not very serious idea\\\".\", \"from\": 2312, \"to\": 2539, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2463, \"end\": 2478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The idea\", \"from\": 2312, \"to\": 2320}, {\"ngram\": \"a show\", \"from\": 2335, \"to\": 2341}, {\"ngram\": \"this magnitude\", \"from\": 2345, \"to\": 2359}, {\"ngram\": \"a large stretch\", \"from\": 2366, \"to\": 2381}, {\"ngram\": \"river\", \"from\": 2385, \"to\": 2390}, {\"ngram\": \"a city\", \"from\": 2394, \"to\": 2400}, {\"ngram\": \"its highest terrorism alert\", \"from\": 2407, \"to\": 2434}, {\"ngram\": \"first thought\", \"from\": 2482, \"to\": 2495}, {\"ngram\": \"a crazy and not very serious idea\", \"from\": 2504, \"to\": 2537}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But this week at the Elys\\u00e9e, the French president said: \\\"We decided it was the right moment to deliver this crazy idea and make it real.\\\"\", \"from\": 2541, \"to\": 2678, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2562, \"end\": 2568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lys\\u00e9e_Palace\", \"score\": 0.9893564130410896, \"rank\": 0.008289473684212503, \"text\": \"Elys\\u00e9e\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/res